OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FNon-dom status: Labour     
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fpledges to replace         
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Ftax-saving scheme          
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Labour has pledged to replace the      
OL,6, so-called "non-dom" taxpayer status in 
OL,7, the UK after a row over the finances of
OL,8, Chancellor Rishi Sunak's wife.         
OL,10,FThe party said it would abolish the    
OL,11,F"unfair" status, which allows UK       
OL,12,Fresidents whose permanent homes are    
OL,13,Fabroad not to pay UK tax on overseas   
OL,14,Fincome.                                
OL,16,FIt would bring in a shorter-term scheme
OL,17,Ffor temporary residents.               
OL,19,FShadow chancellor Rachel Reeves said it
OL,20,Fwould end "outdated tax perks".        
